comments: Lyles (DET) makes marginal contact with Lowry's (MIA) body during his shooting motion that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Strus (MIA) legally contests Joseph (DET) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Haslem (MIA) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Diallo (DET) firms up and absorbs the contact.
Haslem (MIA) sets a back screen on Diallo (DET) and doesn?t give him a step to avoid the contact.
Lowry (MIA) seals Diallo (DET) and affects his ability to pursue the loose ball.
Herro (MIA) slightly extends his leg in a way that is not overt or abrupt. The contact with Joseph (DET) is marginal.
Strus (MIA) makes marginal contact to Joseph's (DET) body at the end of the drive that does not affect his ability to make the pass.
Diallo (DET) legally contests Strus (MIA) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Jackson (DET) dislodges Herro (MIA) from his position during the rebound.
Diallo (DET) moves along Herro's (MIA) path and he absorbs the body contact during the driving shot attempt. Diallo moves his arms into a legal vertical position when the contact occurs.
